SIMPLE: sapphic
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sapphic
<hw>Sap"phic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Sapphicus</ets>, Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ Sappho.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Of or pertaining to Sappho, the Grecian poetess; <as>as,
<ex>Sapphic</ex> odes; <ex>Sapphic</ex> verse</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Pros.)</fld> <def>Belonging to, or in the manner
of, Sappho; -- said of a certain kind of verse reputed to have been
invented by Sappho, consisting of five feet, of which the first, fourth,
and fifth are trochees, the second is a spondee, and the third a
dactyl.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sapphic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sapphic
<hw>Sap"phic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Pros.)</fld> <def>A Sapphic
verse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sapphire</ent>⟦br⟧
